               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_107027">Clapcote</placeName>.
                             
                            Indenture by which <persName>
                           <forename>Roger</forename> 
                           <surname>Badecok</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_107073">W<supplied>allingford</supplied>
                           </placeName>
                        </persName> grants to <persName nymRef="Badecok">
                           <forename>Alice</forename> his daughter</persName> 5 scattered acres of arable land in <placeName key="place_107027">C<supplied>lapcote</supplied> by Wallingford</placeName>, (1) is forera, at <placeName type="minor">la Punde</placeName> by <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> le <surname>Arblaster</surname>
                        </persName>’s land on the south, reaching east to <placeName type="minor">la Greneweye</placeName> which leads to <placeName type="minor">Hodesbot</placeName>, (2) between the land late of <persName>Sir <forename>William</forename> de <surname>Bereford</surname>, kt.</persName>, on either side, reaching to <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> of <surname>Melebourne</surname>
                        </persName>’s land towards the north <pb n="139"/> Mill, and called <placeName type="minor">la Forsshetase</placeName>, (3) ½ acre between the land late of <persName>
                           <forename>Henry</forename> 
                           <surname>Ywon</surname>
                        </persName> on either side, at <placeName type="minor">le Flexlond</placeName>, reaching to the lynche towards <placeName type="minor">Shillingford bridge</placeName>, ½ acre between the land of <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> le <surname>Deyar</surname>’, merchant</persName>, and that of <persName>
                           <forename>Henry</forename> 
                           <surname>Ywon</surname>
                        </persName>, reaching to the said lynche, (4) in the shot called <placeName type="minor">Stomforlong</placeName> between <persName>
                           <forename>Eustace</forename> 
                           <surname>Clements</surname>
                        </persName>’ land and that of <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> de <surname>Louches</surname>
                        </persName>, (5) one acre in <placeName type="minor">Middelforlong</placeName> between the land late of <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> du <surname>char</surname>
                        </persName> and that of <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> le <surname>arblaster</surname>
                        </persName>, reaching to <placeName type="minor">le Russhepathe</placeName> towards the west. Rent: 10 qrs. of barley. 
                            Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> de <surname>Louches</surname>
                        </persName>,
                            <persName nymRef="Notele">
                           <forename>John</forename> son of <persName>
                              <forename>Osbert</forename> of <surname>Notele</surname>
                           </persName>
                        </persName>,
                            <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Badecoke</surname>
                        </persName>, 
                            <persName>
                           <forename>Gilbert</forename> du <surname>char</surname>
                        </persName>,
                            <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> le <surname>cripse</surname>
                        </persName>, 
                            <persName nymRef="Rossel">
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> son of <forename>Alan</forename> 
                           <surname>Rossel</surname>
                        </persName>,
                            <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>Bone</surname>
                        </persName>. 
                            Given at <placeName role="date" key="place_107073">W<supplied>allingford</supplied>
                        </placeName>. 
                            <origDate when="1327-11-01">
                           <supplied>1 Nov. 1327.</supplied>
                        </origDate> 
                            Berks. ch. 69b. is the otherhalf of this indenture. </p>
